# ${title}

This Space hosts a [nebo](https://github.com/nebo-dev/nebo) daemon — a multi-modal
logging dashboard with a live web UI, MCP server, and HTTP API.

## Connect from Python

```python
import nebo as nb

nb.init(
    url="https://${space_url}",
    api_token="<your NEBO_API_TOKEN>",
)

@nb.fn()
def step():
    nb.log("hello from a remote Space")
    nb.log_line("loss", 0.42)

step()
```

The token must match the `NEBO_API_TOKEN` Space secret. To rotate it,
edit the secret in this Space's Settings panel.

## Embed a slice anywhere

```html
<iframe src="https://${space_url}/?run=<run-id>&token=<token>" width="100%" height="600"></iframe>
```

Slice flags: `&dag`, `&logs`, `&metrics`, `&metric=loss`, `&images`,
`&image=hero.png`, `&audios`, `&audio=bell.wav`. Combine with `&node=<func>`
to filter to one node.

## HTTP API

Every endpoint at `https://${space_url}/...` accepts the same JSON
shapes as a local daemon. Read endpoints: `GET /runs`, `/runs/{id}`,
`/runs/{id}/graph`, `/runs/{id}/metrics`, etc. Write events: `POST
/events`. Pass the token via the `X-Nebo-Token` header or `?token=`
query parameter on every request.
